==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Majolica
<hw>Ma*jol"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety> <def>A
kind of pottery, with opaque glazing and showy decoration, which reached
its greatest perfection in Italy in the 16th century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term is said to be derived from Majorca, which was
an early seat of this manufacture.</note> <rj><au>Heyse.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Major</ent>⟦br⟧
